'''John Milhiser''' (born November 29, 1981)<ref name="nbc"/> is an [[Americans|American]] actor and comedian who was a cast member on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' for the [[Saturday Night Live (season 39)|2013–2014 season]].<ref name=new>{{cite web | last =Abramovich | first =Seth | title =Cheat Sheet: Get to Know the 5 New Faces of 'SNL' | work =The Live Feed | publisher =The Hollywood Reporter | date =11 September 2013 | url =http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/saturday-night-live-get-know-625783 | accessdate = 7 October 2013}}</ref>
==Career== He has been a regular performer at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theater]] since 2005, where he was a member of the sketch comedy group Serious Lunch, who have been featured on ''[[Late Night with Jimmy Fallon]]'' and ''[[Attack of the Show]]''. Milhiser is a native of [[Belle Mead, New Jersey]] and he graduated from [[Montgomery High School (New Jersey)|Montgomery High School]] in [[Skillman, New Jersey]]. He later attended [[Hofstra University]], where he graduated in 2004 as a Film Studies and Production major<ref>{{cite web | last =Walter | first =Geoffrey | title =Hofstra Graduate Cast on New Season of 'SNL' | work =Bellmore Patch: News: Around Bellmore | publisher =Patch | date =17 September 2013 | url =http://bellmore.patch.com/groups/around-town/p/hofstra-graduate-cast-on-new-season-of-snl | accessdate = 7 October 2013}}</ref> and was a member of [[Sigma Pi]] fraternity.<ref>{{cite web |title =Notable Alumni - Sigma Pi Fraternity|publisher =Sigma Pi Fraternity| url =https://sigmapi.org/notable-alumni/}}</ref>
Milhiser made his debut on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on the September 28, 2013 season premiere hosted by [[Tina Fey]] with musical guest [[Arcade Fire]]. His celebrity impressions included [[Jon Cryer]], [[Matthew McConaughey]], [[Verne Troyer]] (as Mini-Me from the ''Austin Powers'' movies), [[Justin Timberlake]], and [[Billie Joe Armstrong]]. On July 15, 2014, it was announced that Milhiser's contract with ''SNL'' was not renewed and he would not be returning as a cast member.<ref name="avclub">{{Cite news |url=http://www.avclub.com/article/noel-wells-and-john-milhiser-are-also-leaving-satu-206958 |title=Noël Wells and John Milhiser Are Also Leaving ''Saturday Night Live'' |last=O'Neal |first=Sean |date=July 15, 2014 |work=[[The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=July 19, 2014}}</ref>
In 2014, Milhiser appeared in a supporting role in the indie film ''[[Camp Takota]]'' starring comedians [[Grace Helbig]], [[Hannah Hart]] and [[Mamrie Hart]]. He has also made guest appearances on television programs such as ''[[Adam Ruins Everything]]'', ''[[2 Broke Girls]]'', [[Love (TV series)|Netflix Original Series ''Love'']], and ''[[Other Space]]''.
==Personal life== {{expand section|date=March 2018}} Milhiser is ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''{{'}}s second openly [[homosexuality|gay]] male cast member (after [[Terry Sweeney]]);<ref name="tweet">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JohnMilhiser/status/974796109775216640|title=John Milhiser on Twitter: &quot;Hey, @thedailybeast I’m pretty sure that I was out and proud as a gay man when I was an SNL cast member for a hot sec. 2nd after Terry. There should be more though. Go see @lovesimonmovie !!! :)&quot;|work=[[Twitter]]|last=Milhiser|first=John|date=March 16, 2018|accessdate=March 23, 2018}}</ref> as well as the fourth [[LGBT]] cast member overall (along with [[Danitra Vance]] and [[Kate McKinnon]]).<ref name="advocate">{{cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/comedy/2016/8/22/brief-lgbt-history-saturday-night-live?pg=full|title=A Brief LGBT History of 'Saturday Night Live'|work=[[The Advocate]]|publisher=[[Here Media]]|last=Pierce|first=Robbie X|date=August 22, 2016|accessdate=March 23, 2018}}</ref>
